{
  "title": "Getting Started",
  "slug": "getting-started",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Getting Started"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Moatlog runs inside your project. Install the CLI, run one init command, restart Cursor, and your agent starts building behavioral memory automatically."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": 1,
      "title": "Install",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Install the Moatlog CLI globally, or run commands with npx without installing."
        },
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "npm install -g @moatlog/cli",
          "description": "Install the moatlog CLI globally"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            { "type": "text", "value": "No install needed: " },
            { "type": "inlineCode", "value": "npx @moatlog/cli init" },
            { "type": "text", "value": " works from any project directory." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": 2,
      "title": "Init",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "From your project root, run init. This scaffolds everything Moatlog needs in one step — no manual hook scripts, MCP config, or cursor rules."
        },
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "moatlog init",
          "description": "Scaffold hooks, MCP config, rules, and .moatlog/"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "init creates:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "ordered": false,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                { "type": "inlineCode", "value": ".cursor/hooks.json" },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": " and hook scripts — capture reads, edits, prompts, and shell commands"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                { "type": "inlineCode", "value": ".cursor/mcp.json" },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": " — wires the Moatlog MCP server into Cursor"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                { "type": "inlineCode", "value": ".cursor/rules/moatlog.mdc" },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": " — tells agents to call get_task_context at session start"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                { "type": "inlineCode", "value": ".moatlog/" },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": " — event log directory (added to .gitignore)"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            { "type": "text", "value": "Existing files are skipped. Pass " },
            { "type": "inlineCode", "value": "--force" },
            { "type": "text", "value": " to overwrite." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "variant": "info",
          "title": "Claude Code",
          "text": "For Claude Code, pass --agent claude-code or --agent all: moatlog init --agent all. Then restart Claude Code so hooks and MCP reload."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": 3,
      "title": "Restart Cursor",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Restart Cursor so hooks and MCP reload. Without a restart, the agent won't capture events or connect to get_task_context."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "variant": "info",
          "title": "jq is required for hooks",
          "text": "Hook scripts use jq to parse Cursor hook payloads. Install jq if init warns it is missing on your PATH."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": 4,
      "title": "Verify",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Confirm hooks are active and check moat strength."
        },
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "moatlog status",
          "description": "Show hooks status and moat strength"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You should see ● hooks active (.cursor/hooks.json). Work in Agent mode for a few minutes, then check again — depth and coverage grow as events accumulate."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            { "type": "text", "value": "The stop hook runs " },
            { "type": "inlineCode", "value": "moatlog distill" },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " automatically. Run it manually anytime, or validate freshness with "
            },
            { "type": "inlineCode", "value": "moatlog check-moat" },
            { "type": "text", "value": " before committing moat.json." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "variant": "success",
      "title": "Your moat is now building automatically with every Cursor session",
      "text": "Each prompt, file read, and edit deepens behavioral memory. Distill on stop keeps moat.json current for MCP and your team."
    }
  ]
}
